2025-11-06 | Implement atoi() — String to Integer Conversion

Problem Statement
Given a string s, convert it into an integer without using any built-in conversion functions.

The conversion must follow the rules of the classic atoi() function:
	1.	Ignore leading whitespaces.
	2.	Check for a sign (+ or -) — default to positive if not present.
	3.	Convert consecutive digits into an integer until a non-digit character is encountered.
	4.	Ignore leading zeros during conversion.
	5.	Clamp the result to the 32-bit integer range:
	•	Minimum = -2³¹ = -2147483648
	•	Maximum = 2³¹ - 1 = 2147483647
	6.	If no digits are found, return 0.

Approach / Explanation
	1.	Skip Whitespaces:
	•	Traverse until a non-space character is found.
	2.	Check for Sign:
	•	If you encounter '-', mark number as negative.
	•	If '+', mark number as positive.
	3.	Read Digits:
	•	Continue parsing digits while they are valid ('0'–'9').
	•	Stop when a non-digit is found.
	4.	Handle Overflow:
	•	Before multiplying by 10 or adding a digit, check if the result would overflow.
	5.	Return Final Value:
	•	Apply the sign and clamp the result if necessary.


SOLUTION:

#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    int myAtoi(string &s) {
        int i = 0, n = s.size();
        long long ans = 0;
        bool negative = false;

        //Skip leading whitespaces
        while (i < n && s[i] == ' ')
            i++;

        //Check for sign
        if (i < n && (s[i] == '-' || s[i] == '+')) {
            negative = (s[i] == '-');
            i++;
        }

       // Parse digits
        while (i < n && isdigit(s[i])) {
            int digit = s[i] - '0';

            //Check for overflow before adding digit
            if (ans > (INT_MAX - digit) / 10) {
                return negative ? INT_MIN : INT_MAX;
            }

            ans = ans * 10 + digit;
            i++;
        }

        //Apply sign and return
        if (negative) ans = -ans;
        if (ans > INT_MAX) return INT_MAX;
        if (ans < INT_MIN) return INT_MIN;

        return (int)ans;
    }
};
